## 4. Regional Market Dynamics

Pennsylvania is divided into nine rating areas. While the statewide average rate increase is 21.5%, local market conditions vary.

*   **Rating Area 3 (Northeast/Poconos):** This region exhibits the widest disparity in carrier rates. In 2026, Oscar Health Plan received approval for a 23.1% increase, while Partners Insurance Company received approval for a 10.1% decrease (Pennsylvania Insurance Department, 2025).
*   **Rating Area 6 (Lehigh Valley/Central PA):** This area is experiencing a specific network disruption unrelated to ACA subsidies. A contract dispute between UnitedHealthcare and Lehigh Valley Health Network (LVHN) has affected network status. Medicare Advantage members lost in-network access on January 26, 2026. Commercial plan members, including those in the VA Community Care Network, face loss of in-network access effective April 26, 2026 (Pennsylvania Department of Aging, 2026; WFMZ, 2026).
*   **Rural Areas (Areas 2, 5, 9):** Rural counties, such as Fulton, Juniata, and Potter, face thinner carrier competition. Fifteen of the twenty counties with the highest proportional coverage loss are rural (Pennie, 2026a).

